                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(2)\">My dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have written this by the special request of the most\n                respect<lb/>able members of the <placeName>Charleston</placeName> reformed Synagogue\n                with the view if<lb/> possible to stop the, so called, progress some of their\n                members are bent<lb/> on making which, it is clear, will ultimately lay Judaism\n                prostrate<lb/> The promoters of this, who are also your sincere friends, trust\n                that<lb/> you will give this an insertion at your earliest opportunity, for<lb/>\n                their sakes as well as for the sake of the upholding our Religion gen<lb/>erally,\n                and that you will not spare your own able pen in support<lb/>\n                <add>?</add> the principles advocated herein. The <persName>Revd Mr\n                    Nathan</persName> of<placeName> N. O</placeName><lb/>\n                <add>?</add> kindly taken the trouble to copy it and has prepared this for\n                    <add>?</add><lb/> with my alterations and additions thereto you can do as you please<lb/>\n                <sic>Whereever</sic> I came I found your prospectus in the hands of your\n                friends<lb/> who I am happy to inform you are very many <add>ודי לחכימא\n                ברמיזא</add><lb/> I am now on my return to <placeName>New York</placeName> and hope\n                to have the pleasure soon<lb/> to see you Remaining my dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">yours faithfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">S. Newman</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ff3mk8k/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
